Immediate past honourable Minister of Transport, Rotimi Amaechi, while speaking with delegates at the APC Special Convention on Tuesday night, stated that he is the most experienced of all the candidates vying to become the All Progressives Congress (APC) Presidential flagbearer at the 2023 general elections. Amaechi, while speaking at the Eagle Square, challenged the delegates not to vote for him if he has not performed in the past. He also listed in chronological order, the past offices he has held, both elected and appointed, highlighting his achievements in office in his attempt to convince the party delegates to cast their votes for him. The immediate past Transportation Minister also urged the delegates to vote their consciences as they go on to cast their votes at the APC Presidential Primary.